#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:1
msgid "Fix issues with VTK / VTK-m array conversion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:3
msgid ""
"Changed the VTK to VTK-m array conversion routines to use "
"`ArrayHandleRuntimeVec` and `ArrayHandleRecombineVec`. These are new "
"features of VTK-m that allow you to specify an array with the tuple size "
"specified at runtime. This change improves several specific things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:8
msgid ""
"Fixes a bug when importing an array of \"odd\" tuple size (not 1, 2, 3, 4, "
"6, or 9). It was creating arrays of size one less than the actual size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:11
msgid ""
"Avoids using `ArrayHandleGroupVecVariable`, which is supported by fewer VTK-"
"m filters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:13
msgid ""
"The VTK-m `ArrayHandle` now manages a reference back to the VTK array, so "
"the `ArrayHandle` will continue to work even if the original VTK array is "
"\"deleted.\" This makes the code safer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:16
msgid ""
"Unifies the implementation of the array conversion among number of "
"components to avoid issues with surprise tuple sizes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/corrected-vtk-vtkm-transfers.md:18
msgid ""
"Revamped vtkmDataArray to support general array types. This makes it more "
"efficient to pass data from VTK-m to VTK when unified memory is not "
"available."
msgstr ""
